div.p:
A Sixth Argument;

                     Arg. 6 All means of Grace and Salvation which God hath appointed as inſtrumetal to that end, are to be afforded to Infants, which they are ſuſceptive or receptive and capable of (this no rational perſon will deny) For when God hath appointed the means to any end, we are tied to the uſe thereof; if we

expect to attain to that end; as I might inſtance in divers particulars: But Baptiſm is a means of Grace and ſalvation, which Infants are receptive and capable of, and therefore it is to be afforded and miniſtred unto them.
